Ontology(<https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts>
<https://github.com/jonathanvajda/2025-05-24/cco-d-acts>
Import(<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/2024-11-06/CommonCoreOntologiesMerged>)
Annotation(<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title> "CCO-Conformant Document Acts Ontology"@en)
Annotation(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> "Jonathan M. Vajda")
Annotation(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The Common Core Ontologies (CCO) Conformant Documents Ontology is a domain ontology that represents the generic domain of entities relevant to the creation, modification, or termination of social arrangements by means of some document. This includes social acts, deontic roles, and directive information and information bearing entities."@en)
Annotation(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <https://opensource.org/license/BSD-3-Clause>)
Annotation(rdfs:comment "CCO-D-Acts is designed to fill a gap in representation of social, legal, normative, and deontic entities for ontologies that rely on the Common Core Ontologies (CCO) suite (https://github.com/CommonCoreOntology/CommonCoreOntologies). Within the Basic Formal Ontology (BFO) ecosystem, the Document Acts (D-Acts) ontology (https://github.com/d-acts/d-acts) is an extension of the OBO Foundry Information Artifact Ontology (IAO). This ontology proposes to transpose that OBO ontology into a CCO equivalent."@en)
Annotation(rdfs:comment "The most recent version of this file is always hosted on GitHub https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts"@en)
Annotation(rdfs:label "CCO-Conformant Document Acts Ontology"@en)
Annotation(owl:versionInfo "2025-05-24"@en)

