# Class: <https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts/ont00000053> (Legal Party Proxy Role)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts/ont00000053> "Attorney vs lawyer vs other role (consider nuances in who can represent a client in court) -- preparations of a brief, for example, might require an advocate who is distinct	"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts/ont00000053> "Legal Party Proxy Role"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts/ont00000053> "Legal Client Representative Role"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts/ont00000053> "deontic role that is ... acting on behalf of some person or group of persons	"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts/ont00000053> "realized in speaking to a court official on behalf of some party; realized in maintaining confidentiality with respect to some subject matter"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts/ont00000053> <https://github.com/jonathanvajda/cco-d-acts/ont00000004>)

